ClickPaper approvals are ClickPaper approvals for November Please note that the credit limits in the spreadsheet reflect onetenth of the actual credit limit that we have assigned for a given counterparty since the headroom within ClickPaper is calculated using Sigma Factor Volume rather than Pprice Volume We will assign all future limits by using onetenth of the assigned credit limit since using the Sigma factor in these calculations generates a value of roughly onetenth of the full limit Hopefully this will eliminate some of the recent problems weve had with counterparties busting their credit limits Please call or send a note if you have any questions Thanks Walter

Re ClickPaper approvals Cc Thanks for the info Ill amend the PG status to include physical only until we hear something that makes us more comfortable trading financially Walter To Walter NRON cc Tom CT Tana CT Subject Re ClickPaper approvals We may want to rethink allowing PG to trade on Clickpaper for financial business We have been trying to negotiate an ISDA with PG for well over a year to no avail While they are a great credit they have issues with our no reliance clause in our documents which is a HUGE legal issue and they were involved in a large derivative lawsuit with Bankers Trust several years ago This may be one for legal to decide but my vote is against until there is an ISDA to confirm trades under Thanks Tanya Walter NRON AM To Camille NRON Mary G CT Samuel CT Adnan NRON Tanya CT Paul NRON Tom CT Bradley CT Tana CT Karen CT Frank L CT Noel nron Walter nron cc Subject ClickPaper approvals Attached are ClickPaper approvals for December Please call if you have any questions thanks Walter
